  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "The 2018 hardback Visions of Heresy re-presents the four original art volumes — War, Darkness, Treachery, Death — and the short story 'The Kaban Project' by Graham McNeill in the layout of Forge World's Heresy black-books. Alan Merrett's original text, revised and extended by Guy Haley, threads concept art, illustration, and new Neil Roberts pieces into a chronological reference for the civil war that breaks Horus Lupercal's loyalty and shatters the Emperor's Legiones Astartes — Isstvan III's purge, the Drop Site Massacre at Isstvan V, and the long road to the siege of Terra. 'The Kaban Project' shadows Mechanicum adept Pallas Ravachol as he uncovers a sentient war-machine commissioned for the Warmaster and is hunted across Mars for knowing it lives.",
